2006.","meanings":["From the Latin name <i>Caecilia</i>, feminine form of <i>Caecilius</i> (  see  Cecil  ). This was a good deal more common than the masculine form, largely due to the fame of the 2nd- or 3rd-century virgin martyr whose name is still mentioned daily in the Roman Catholic Canon of the Mass. She is regarded as the patron saint of music and has inspired works such as  Purcell's  ‘Ode on St Cecilia's Day’, although the reasons for this association are not clear."],"variants":[{"name":"Cecelia","meanings":["From the Latin name <i>Caecilia</i>, feminine form of <i>Caecilius</i> (  see  Cecil  ). This was a good deal more common than the masculine form, largely due to the fame of the 2nd- or 3rd-century virgin martyr whose name is still mentioned daily in the Roman Catholic Canon of the Mass. She is regarded as the patron saint of music and has inspired works such as  Purcell's  ‘Ode on St Cecilia's Day’, although the reasons for this association are not clear."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Cecilia Birgersdotter was born as the daughter of Birger Job and Margareta. She married Karl Magnusson Läma about 1339. She died after 15 July 1347."},"et":{"–after 15 July 1347":"–pärast 15. juulit 1347","–1347":"–1347","1321–1347":"1321–1347","1340–1407":"1340–1407","1342–1402":"1342–1402","1347–1411":"1347–1411","1283–Male":"1283–Surnud","1287–Female":"1287–Surnud","after 15 July 1347":"pärast 15. juulit 1347","1340":"1340","Abt 1347":"umbes 1347","1283":"1283","abt 1342":"umbes 1342","1402":"1402","1347":"1347","after 1339":"pärast 1339","1411":"1411","abt 1339":"umbes 1339","1321":"1321","1287":"1287","1342":"1342","1407":"1407","15 July 1347":"15. juuli 1347","Brunnsholm, Näs, Uppsala län, Uppland, Sweden":"Brunnsholm, Enköpings-Näs, Uppsala, Rootsi","Of Brunnsholm, Nas, Uppsala, Sweden":"Brunnsholm, Uppsala, Rootsi","of Brunnsholm, Nas, Uppsl, Swdn":"Brunnsholm, Uppsala, Rootsi","Uppsala-Näs, Uppsala, Sweden":"Uppsala-Näs, Uppsala, Rootsi"},"fi":{"–after 15 July 1347":"–